    <note>Wang(2) Keming(2) [22101] He was a famous physician, who was particularly skilled in acupuncture. He used this method to cure the wife of Wei(5) Anxing [1940], who had not risen from her bed in ten years. Keming's funerary inscription provides information about his medical education. His wife, born Wenren, was a Jiaxing native--most, if not all, Song Wenren of note were from Jiaxing, therefore establishing probable affinal linkage. Ye Shi, WJ, 13.243-45. CBD, 1, 293.</note>
